div1.p:
In the District Court holding terms at Seattle Territory of Washington County of King } ss
United States of America -vs- William Jameson} Order for committment of witness

And now on this 22nd day of August 1885, our application of C. H. Hanford, assistant United States District Attorney for Washington Territory, and being satisfied by sufficient proof that Alfred Woods now present is a material witness for the United States in the above entitled cause now pending in this court, and that the testimony of said Alfred Woods is expect and will be necessary on the trial of said cause; It is therefore ordered by me the Judge of the said District Court that said Alfred Woods do give a recognizance in the same at Two Hundrend dollars with sufficient

surities conditional that he appear in this court at hte next term thereof on the first day of said term and from day to day and term to term thereof to until discharged, to testify as a witness for the United States and that in default of bail he he committed to the custody of the United States Marshall

Territoru of Washington, County of King. }ss. I, James Seavey, Clerk of the District Court of the Third Judicial District, Washington Territory, holding terms at Seattle, in King County for the counties of King and Kitsap do hereby certify the foregoing to be true full and correct transcript of the order for commitment of Alfred Woods, witness - in this foregoing entitled cause, now on file, and of record in my office Witness my hand and the Seal of said Court at Seattle this the 22nd day of August A. D. 1885 James Seavey, Clerk. by James P Ludlow, Deputy
FILED Oct 27 1885 James Seavey, Clerk. By James P Ludlow Deputy Clerk.
